%% KubeRay Operator - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User/Client
    participant Gateway as data-science-gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant KRBP as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Dashboard as Ray Dashboard<br/>8265/TCP HTTP
    participant Operator as KubeRay Operator
    participant Head as Ray Head Pod<br/>6379/TCP
    participant Workers as Ray Worker Pods
    participant CertMgr as cert-manager
    participant Redis as Redis (optional)<br/>6379/TCP

    Note over User,Dashboard: Flow 1: Ray Dashboard Access via Gateway API (RHOAI 3.x)
    User->>Gateway: GET /ray/{ns}/{cluster}/*<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    Gateway->>KRBP: Forward request<br/>HTTPS/8443 TLS
    KRBP->>K8sAPI: TokenReview + SubjectAccessReview<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+
    K8sAPI-->>KRBP: Auth result
    KRBP->>Dashboard: Proxy to localhost<br/>HTTP/8265 plaintext (loopback)
    Dashboard-->>KRBP: Dashboard response
    KRBP-->>Gateway: HTTPS response
    Gateway-->>User: HTTPS response

    Note over Operator,Workers: Flow 2: RayJob Submission
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Watch RayJob CR<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: RayJob event
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create/update RayCluster + Job<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+
    Operator->>Dashboard: Submit Ray job<br/>HTTP/8265 plaintext
    Dashboard-->>Operator: Job status
    Head->>Workers: Distribute tasks<br/>TCP/6379 mTLS (if enabled)
    Workers->>Head: Return results<br/>TCP/10001 mTLS (if enabled)
    Head->>Redis: GCS checkpoint (optional)<br/>TCP/6379

    Note over Operator,CertMgr: Flow 3: mTLS Certificate Provisioning
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Issuer + Certificate CRs<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+
    K8sAPI-->>CertMgr: Certificate CR event
    CertMgr->>K8sAPI: Create TLS Secrets<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+
    Note over Head,Workers: Secrets mounted as volumes<br/>CA, head, and worker certs
